                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.7353b W 52/141: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wheeler</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-07-03T11:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 3, 1923—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 12:51 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>264. Your 165, June 30, 2 p.m. The second paragraph of the offer mentioned
                    relates to all traffic originating in South Europe, i.e., the south to be served
                    by the Italian cable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wheeler</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
